# Visual Bible Feature — Auto Narrative Review for Historical Videos

When the **Historical** constraint checkbox is checked, the app will automatically generate a "Visual Bible" document before processing individual segments. This ensures visual consistency across all prompts.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Logic

---

#### [NEW] [narrative_review.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/narrative_review.py)

New module for generating and managing the Visual Bible:

- `generate_visual_bible(srt_path, api_client, log_callback) → str`: Reads full SRT content → sends to API (always **Pro** tier) with a review prompt → returns the Visual Bible text
- `load_visual_bible(output_dir, project_name) → str | None`: Load cached Visual Bible from file if it exists
- `save_visual_bible(output_dir, project_name, content)`: Save Visual Bible to `{output_dir}/{project_name}_visual_bible.txt`

The review prompt will instruct the AI to analyze the full SRT and produce a structured document covering:
1. **Bối cảnh** — Time period, geography
2. **Nhân vật chính** — Each main character with detailed physical description, costume
3. **Nhóm nhân vật chung** — Armies, civilians, etc. with uniforms, weapons, flags
4. **Kiến trúc / Địa điểm** — Buildings, landscapes matching the era

---

#### [NEW] [narrative_review_prompt.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/prompts/narrative_review_prompt.txt)

Prompt template for the Visual Bible generation step. Instructs the AI to analyze all subtitle text and produce detailed, structured context.

---

#### [MODIFY] [process_controller.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/process_controller.py)

In [_process_single_project()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/process_controller.py#174-293):
- Check if `constraints.get("historical")` is True
- If yes:
  1. Try `load_visual_bible()` first (use cached if exists)
  2. If no cache: call `generate_visual_bible()` using **Pro** tier (regardless of user tier setting)
  3. Emit signal to show review popup on main thread (user can edit)
  4. Wait for user to confirm/edit
  5. Call `save_visual_bible()` to save to file
  6. Prepend the Visual Bible to the [style_content](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#45-55) that gets sent with each segment

---

#### [MODIFY] [prompt_generator.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py)

In [_build_user_message()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#156-210):
- Accept optional `visual_bible: str` parameter
- When provided, include it as a `=== VISUAL BIBLE (REFERENCE) ===` section in the user message with clear instructions: "Use this as reference. Only apply information relevant to the current segment."

Update [generate_single()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#101-155), [generate_batch()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#211-243), [_generate_sequential()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#244-301) to pass `visual_bible` through.

---

### UI Layer

---

#### [MODIFY] [main_window.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/main_window.py)

- Add a new signal `_sig_review_bible` to handle Visual Bible review popup
- Add method `_show_visual_bible_review(content, callback)`:
  - Shows a popup with a large **QTextEdit** containing the Visual Bible text
  - User can read and edit the text
  - Two buttons: **"✅ Confirm & Continue"** and **"❌ Cancel"**
  - Returns the (possibly edited) text back to the processing thread

---

## Flow Summary

```
User clicks Start (Historical ✓)
    │
    ▼
For each SRT project:
    │
    ├─ Check cached visual_bible file exists?
    │   ├─ YES → load from file
    │   └─ NO → Send full SRT to API (Pro tier) → get Visual Bible
    │
    ├─ Show Review Popup → User edits/confirms
    │
    ├─ Save visual_bible to file
    │
    └─ Process segments normally, with Visual Bible prepended to each request
```

## Verification Plan

### Manual Testing
Since this is a GUI app with no existing test suite, verification will be manual:

1. **Run the app**: `python main.py` from the project directory
2. **Setup**: Add a SRT file, select a style, set output directory
3. **Test 1 — Historical OFF**: Uncheck Historical, click Start → verify prompts generate normally without Visual Bible step
4. **Test 2 — Historical ON (first run)**: Check Historical, click Start → verify:
   - Log shows "Generating Visual Bible..." message
   - Review popup appears with structured content
   - Can edit text in popup
   - After clicking Confirm, processing continues with normal segment generation
   - `{project_name}_visual_bible.txt` file is saved in output directory
5. **Test 3 — Cached Visual Bible**: Run again with same SRT → verify:
   - Log shows "Loading cached Visual Bible..."
   - Review popup still appears (with cached content)
   - No extra API call needed
6. **Test 4 — Cancel**: Click Cancel on review popup → verify processing skips/stops gracefully
